Senator Mohammed
1 moves to amend the bill on page 1, line 5, by inserting the following at the end of the line before
2 the period:
3 "AND TO ESTABLISH A SCHOLARSHIP FOR CHILDREN OF PERMANENTLY
4 DISABLED OR SLAIN NC LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICERS";
5
6 And on page 7, lines 47-48, by inserting the following between those lines:
7 "SECTION 16.7. The University of North Carolina Board of Governors shall
8 develop a scholarship program for any child, if the child is at least 17 years old but not yet 28
9 years old, whose parent, legal guardian, or legal custodian is a law enforcement officer,
10 correctional officer, firefighter, volunteer firefighter, or rescue squad worker who is permanently
11 and totally disabled as a direct result of a traumatic injury sustained in the line of duty.
12 The scholarship program shall provide assistance with tuition, fees, educational supplies, and
13 boarding expenses not covered under Chapter 115B of the General Statutes and shall be available
14 for both undergraduate and graduate programs.
15 The Board of Governors shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee
16 on the establishment of the program no later than July 1, 2026.".
